    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The process of wrapping a flat, flexible work or material around a cylinder or onto itself for the purpose of storage or transport. Examples include the following: the rolling of scrolls around a rod or onto themselves; the rolling of drawn, painted, printed, or inscribed works on parchment, paper, or canvas; the rolling of textiles, film, or other flexible works or materials. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
